Kr贸le  () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Bartoszyce, within Bartoszyce County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  south-east of Bartoszyce and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
The village has a population of 90.
